Program: Outlook
Title: A Family of Fighters for Human Rights
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02fhmzg
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 2 Jan 2015
Pakistani activist sisters Gulalai and Saba Ismail, founders of Aware Girls, are joined by their father Muhammad to explain why they became campaigners and what their work involves. Also, the 50-year career of Donny Osmond. He started singing in public when he was five years old and is still performing. He remembers the pressures of being a teen idol, and describes how he rebuilt his career after falling out of fashion in the 1980s. Pictures: Pakistani activist sisters Gulalai (L) and Saba Ismail Picture credit: Gulalai: Peace Direct; and Saba: Aware Girls Show less